                        <div><strong>MBBCh, PGA – ART, PGA – Molecular Biology, University of Warwick, UK</strong></div></h6>
                        <p class="card-text mbr-fonts-style align-center display-7">A physician and Molecular Biologist who transitioned to a seasoned entrepreneur and top healthcare management professional with local and international network. A graduate of Medicine from the University of Calabar, Nigeria with two postgraduate studies in Assisted reproduction Technology and Molecular biology from the university of Warwick, UK<br><br>Possess excellent skills in business development, operation, finance, marketing management and strategy; expert in business integration, strategic planning and forecast involving start-ups and already established organizations.<br><br>Effective leader with proven success in new market identification and strategic positioning for multimillion-dollar Molecular Diagnostic and Biotechnology organizations.<br><br>Founded a clinical laboratory company which was restructured in 2016 to service the Nigerian molecular biology market needs. Grew company’s revenue from zero in 2012 to a multimillion dollar company; making it become one of the top 2 leading Molecular Diagnostic and Biotechnology organizations in Nigeria.<br><br>Leads operations and strategic direction of molecular assay development and optimization, assay validation, quality management systems, biosafety and biosecurity of molecular laboratories in line with WHO guidelines.<br><br>Provides cross-functional management: directs Biomedical engineering projects involving structural laboratory design, setting up of molecular laboratory, equipment installation and maintenance, molecular biology training, life science research, logistics and supply chain.<br><br>Established thought leader in the field of Molecular Biology and Biotechnology; who has directly and indirectly mentored thousands of young molecular biologists and biotechnologists.<br><br>Built and maintained professional relationships with domestic partners, potential investors and international partnerships with the world’s leading Biotechnology manufacturing companies.</p>
