                        <p class="card-text mbr-fonts-style align-center display-7">Mohammed Nurat Oluwatomi obtained her B.Sc. in Zoology from the University of Ilorin and after this, developed keen interest in biomedical research and molecular diagnostics; went on to complete and obtained her M.Sc. in Cell biology and Genetics from the prestigious University of Ibadan, and graduated as an exceptional molecular scientist and geneticist<br><br>Nurat is passionate about women and girls’ rights, community health and improved disease diagnostics. Over the past three (3) years she has focused on projects that aim to reduce the burden of disease and discovery of suggestive ways of strengthening health systems of the communities these projects were carried out, she is an experienced molecular techniques trainer, biomedical researcher, and academic tutor.<br><br>Nurat has worked with different research groups and herself conducted series of experiments that involve DNA extraction, Polymerase chain reaction, Gel electrophoresis, SDS PAGE and ELISA. Her knowledge of molecular biology  are reliable in clinical testing, research, review and validation.</p>
